HEADWORD: Pentadelphous
<hw>Pen`ta*del"phous</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧n`t⟦adot⟧*d⟦ecr⟧l"f⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Penta-</ets> + Gr. <grk>'adelfo`s</grk>
brother.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having the stamens arranged in
five clusters, those of each cluster having their filaments more or less
united, as the flowers of the linden.</def>⟦br⟧
